Excess requirements for public procurement applications are excluded by law
The legislation may establish exhaustive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session of the plenary session, the State Dumas plan to consider in the second reading a bill establishing the requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, which can be attended only by small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On purchases of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities".
The draft law was developed in compliance with the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium-sized Enterprises in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on a comprehensive list of documents that customers have the right to request in the form of an application from procurement participants - small and medium-sized enterprises.
And also the list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities" regulates the procurement activities of certain types of legal entities.
The requirements for the content, form, design and composition of the application for participation in the procurement shall be established by the customers independently in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, the customers establish excessive requirements for the content, registration of the application, the mandatory presence in its composition of certificates, certificates, statements, the period of receipt of which in the authorized bodies is comparable with the period of submission of applications, which leads to the impossibility of participation in such purchase and reduction in the purchase price," the law reads.
The new bill provides for the establishment of a comprehensive list of documents that customers have the right to request in the form of an application from the participants of the purchase, who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises.
"The adoption of the document will eliminate the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises," the explanatory note says.
