Moscow authorities told about the fate of the closed landfills
In the Moscow region, landfills of solid household waste continue to be closed.
This year, the authorities have promised to eliminate the latter.
Some of the 39 existing landfills are being modernized into modern must-processing complexes.
But this option is not possible for every landfill - many of them have grown into a dense residential development.
After the landfill is closed, it gets up for recultivation - the body of the landfill is sprinkled with soil, the degassing and draining systems are installed.
This makes it possible to stop the chemical processes inside the landfill, so that it does not ignite, does not effluent, does not poison the soil and groundwater.
And then the former dump remains to be raised by a useless pile among the surrounding housing.
Why not make it something useful?
For example, in Ruse, where the recultivation of the Annino site was literally completed the other day, the authorities are considering the option of making a pile of ski slopes.
This landfill, which operated from 1976 to 2016, has grown so much that it has gone beyond the boundaries of the land allocated to it.
Therefore, during recultivation, it was necessary to buy out the neighboring areas, which have been de facto littered for a long time.
“Some time will pass, the field will ‘sit down’, fortresses will be built, and we will think what can be done so that it begins to benefit.
Right in the eyes - a ski resort ", - told journalists the head of the Ruz district Nikolay Parfenov.
