Degtyarev surprised by information about the purchase of Sakhalin-1 gas for dollars
On Sunday, July 26, Mikhail Degtyarev, acting governor of Khabarovsk Territory, during a meeting with residents of Soviet Havana, was surprised that the region is buying Sakhalin gas produced by the American company Exxon Neftegas for dollars.
U.S. gas is contracted in dollars until 2025.
To be honest, I didn’t know that, and I’m in such a downpour because of that information.
I had no idea what would happen in Russia in 2020,” he told RIA Novosti.
Degtyarev noted that this issue was discussed with the head of the Russian Ministry of Energy Alexander Novak during his visit to Khabarovsk on July 24.
The governor also stressed that by 2025, “Gazprom” will switch to the supply of Russian power plants and capacities, which means that Russian gas purchased in rubles will be used “at normal prices”.
The Sakhalin-1 project is implemented through a product-sharing agreement, where Exxon Neftegas Ltd is the project operator with a 30% stake, another 20% at Rosneft, Sodeco Japan with 30% and ONGC India with 20%.
The Khabarovsk Territory has been acquiring gas from this project since 2005.
