The actor of the Russian series responded to the accusations of "propaganda of LGBT and feminism"
The actor of the Russian series “Chicago”, whose creators were accused of “promoting LGBT and feminism”, responded to the claims to the film.
The authors “understood the sharpness of the raised themes and did not want to offend anyone,” said the American Steven Thomas Oxner in an interview with the publication “The Rise.”
“I think it’s a story about power and the general aspects of human life.
This has nothing to do with LGBT and feminism,” said the actor who played the father of the boy who changed into a woman’s outfit.
He said he was “proud of the job” and did not consider it propaganda.
At the same time, the American added, he is frightened by the reaction of some people to the plot line of the series: for example, there was a case when "a man in a deep breath shot the set and said that all this is not true."
“Then there were a couple of cases where we met disgruntled locals who didn’t understand what we were doing.
But we were open, so the people who first came with the claims began to help us,” he summed up.
The case of the shooting, the publication explains, occurred in September 2019 in Kabardino-Balkaria: a drunk man attacked the car of the shooting group with a gun, after which he was detained by police officers.
Earlier it was reported that the public representative for the protection of the family Olga Baranets sent a complaint to the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Roskomnadzor on the service more.tv, which hosted the Russian series "Chiki".
Baranets accused the creators of the series of "propaganda of unconventional sexual relations and feminism", noting that the main characters of the film work as prostitutes, and the series itself contains "scenes of physical and psychological violence".
The ombudsman was also outraged by the fact that "the series pays a lot of attention to the homosexual sexual orientation" of the minor character.
The comedy drama "Chicago" tells about three prostitutes who started a new life and opened a business on the advice of a friend.
